A man committed suicide in Tetu, Nyeri on Monday after attempting to kill his wife over domestic squabble. Area police boss Job Lesinikwa said Maina Maranga, 50, slashed his wife Susan Wanjiku after an argument. Lesinikwa said the father of seven took his life for fear of being lynched by the locals. Locals jammed at the home and managed to save the woman who sustained several injuries. She was admitted to Nyeri Outspan Hospital while the man's body was taken to Nyeri Referral hospital mortuary. A neighbour said the man and his wife, both traders, had a long-standing domestic dispute. Click here for the latest political news 